  "original_title": "22\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf \u0dc3\u0d82\u0dc1\u0ddd\u0db0\u0db1\u0dba \u0db1\u0ddc\u0db4\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "22nd Amendment to the Constitution to Parliament immediately",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The 22nd Amendment to the Constitution, which has been approved by the Cabinet of Ministers, will be gazetted and presented to Parliament in the next few days, Minister of Justice, Prisons and Constitutional Reform said at a media briefing held at the Government Information Department today (28). Seven days after the bill was gazetted, it will be placed on the agenda of Parliament and further action will be taken, the Minister said.",
        "The Minister said that the people have a problem with the number of amendments to the Constitution. Explaining this, the Minister said, \u201cAfter the Samagi Janabalawegaya presented the 21st Amendment Bill to Parliament, I introduced the 22nd Amendment to the Constitution as a private member's motion. When I was appointed as a Minister, I presented the same constitutional amendment to the Cabinet as a draft constitutional amendment to the government.",
        "The Minister said that there is dancing. At the same time, the 22nd Amendment to the Constitution, which I personally tabled, was withdrawn from Parliament. As a government proposal it will publish the 22nd Amendment to the Constitution in the Gazette and present it to Parliament.",
        "Considering the original Amendment Bill to be taken up in the process of this in Parliament, it will be renamed as No. 21. Accordingly, when the 22nd Amendment is first debated in Parliament, it will be named as the 21st Amendment to the Constitution.",
        "The 21st Amendment to the Constitution tabled by the Opposition is unworkable. The Supreme Court has ruled that a referendum is required for every clause to become law. \u201d"
      ],
